cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about video object segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel deep sorting network, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper addresses the problem of learning to suggest the single best frame, which involves decision-making and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. The paper also deals with video data, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, the paper uses a performance-based loss function, which involves optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category.
